msgctxt "talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to the <2.se_co>Swallow's Roost<3.re_co>, the\n"
"finest inn this side of Death Mountain!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to the <2.se_co>Swallow's Roost<3.re_co>, the\n"
"finest inn you will ever step foot in.<4.pa>\n"
"You must be tired at this late hour."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Haven't you seen it?<2.pa>\n"
"That <3.se_co>monster<4.re_co> just appeared one day.\n"
"\n"
"It's been terrorizing the village nonstop.\n"
"We can't take much more of this."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Ever since that <2.se_co>monster<3.re_co> appeared above\n"
"the village, there have been new victims\n"
"every day."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Heh...<2.pa> If you want a place to stay,\n"
"talk to the innkeeper."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid "<1.so>Come back soon!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to the <2.se_co>Swallow's Roost<3.re_co>,\n"
"voted best (and only) inn in Rito Village.<4.pa>\n"
"Looks like you got caught in the rain."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Look, I'm just running my mouth here.<2.pa>\n"
"If you want to know the details, talk to\n"
"the <3.se_co>elder<4.re_co> on the top floor."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Our inn is the perfect place to snooze\n"
"your troubles away!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid "<1.so>I will not keep youâ€”<2.pa>go get some rest."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I decided to take a break.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Today has been dead anyway, what with\n"
"that <3.se_co>monster flying around <4.re_co>up there."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>All right. I gotta get back to work.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Hey, buddy. You should stop by and\n"
"take a load off. I work at the\n"
"<2.se_co>Swallow's Roost<3.re_co>!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid "<1.so>Oh... <2.pa>You're a traveler."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>We were just chatting about <2.se_co>that\n"
"monster in the sky<3.re_co>. You know,\n"
"<4.se_co>Divine Beast Vah Medoh<5.re_co>.\n"
"Turns out that a long, long time ago,\n"
"that thing was on our side."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Right. <2.pa>A long time ago, the Champion of\n"
"Rito Village,<3.pa> Revali, tamed <4.se_co>that beast<5.re_co> and\n"
"used it to protect the village.\n"
"...According to the elder, at least.<6.pa>\n"
"And I believe him!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So the story goes, but why did it start\n"
"attacking us now?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey, there!<2.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Business is slow right now, thanks to\n"
"<3.se_co>Divine Beast Vah Medoh <4.re_co>up there.\n"
"It's really ruining my commissions!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Long ago, the village Champion, Revali,\n"
"tamed that <2.se_co>thing <3.re_co>and used it to protect\n"
"the village."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hah! <2.pa>He acts like a know-it-all even\n"
"though he simply regurgitates what the\n"
"<3.se_co>elder <4.re_co>says."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Luck is on your side, pal!<2.pa>\n"
"The village has finally quieted down after\n"
"all the commotion from the <3.se_co>sky monster<4.re_co>. "
msgstr ""

